{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.36",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 36 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:1",
      "text": "There shall no evil happen unto him that feareth the Lord; but in temptation even again he will deliver him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:2",
      "text": "A wise man hateth not the law; but he that is an hypocrite therein is as a ship in a storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:3",
      "text": "A man of understanding trusteth in the law; and the law is faithful unto him, as an oracle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:4",
      "text": "Prepare what to say, and so thou shalt be heard: and bind up instruction, and then make answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:5",
      "text": "The heart of the foolish is like a cartwheel; and his thoughts are like a rolling axle-tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:6",
      "text": "A stallion horse is as a mocking friend, he neigheth under every one that sitteth upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:7",
      "text": "Why doth one day excel another, when as all the light of every day in the year is of the sun?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:8",
      "text": "By the knowledge of the Lord they were distinguished: and he altered seasons and feasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:9",
      "text": "Some of them hath he made high days, and hallowed them, and some of them hath he made ordinary days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:10",
      "text": "And all men are from the ground, and Adam was created of earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:11",
      "text": "In much knowledge the Lord hath divided them, and made their ways diverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:12",
      "text": "Some of them hath he blessed and exalted, and some of them hath he sanctified, and set near himself: but some of them hath he cursed and brought low, and turned out of their places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:13",
      "text": "As the clay is in the potter's hand, to fashion it at his pleasure: so man is in the hand of him that made him, to render to them as liketh him best.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:14",
      "text": "Good is set against evil, and life against death: so is the godly against the sinner, and the sinner against the godly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:15",
      "text": "So look upon all the works of the most High; and there are two and two, one against another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:16",
      "text": "Though I was the last to wake up, yet I received their inheritance as from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:17",
      "text": "O Lord have mercy upon the people that is called by thy name, and upon Israel, whom thou hast named thy firstborn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:18",
      "text": "O be merciful unto Jerusalem, thy holy city, the place of thy rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:19",
      "text": "Fill Sion with thine unspeakable oracles, and thy people with thy glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:20",
      "text": "Give testimony unto those that thou hast possessed from the beginning, and raise up prophets that have been in thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:21",
      "text": "Reward them that wait for thee, and let thy prophets be found faithful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:22",
      "text": "O Lord, hear the prayer of thy servants, according to the blessing of Aaron over thy people, that all they which dwell upon the earth may know that thou art the Lord, the eternal God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:23",
      "text": "The belly devoureth all meats, yet is one meat better than another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:24",
      "text": "As the palate tasteth divers kinds of venison: so doth an heart of understanding false speeches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:25",
      "text": "A froward heart causeth heaviness: but a man of experience will recompense him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:26",
      "text": "A woman will receive every man, yet is one daughter better than another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:27",
      "text": "The beauty of a woman cheereth the countenance, and a man loveth nothing better.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:28",
      "text": "If there be kindness, meekness, and comfort, in her tongue, then is not her husband like other men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:29",
      "text": "He that getteth a wife beginneth a possession, a help like unto himself, and a pillar of rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:30",
      "text": "Where no hedge is, there the possession is spoiled: and he that hath no wife will wander up and down mourning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.36.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 36:31",
      "text": "Who will trust a thief well appointed, that skippeth from city to city? so [who will believe] a man that hath no house, and lodgeth wheresoever the night taketh him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
